attribution: Provided by the Library of Congress
description: Ms., very probably of Parisian manufacture. In Latin. Title from spine of ca. 1800 binding. The book is in a slipcase lettered: Livre d'heures de la reine Jeanne de Naples. The slipcased book is in a case (15 x 7 x 4 cm.) with separate compartment for a magnifying glass. Lettered on case: To Edith from Lessing August 9, 1951. For detailed description see Schutzner. Schutzner, S. Medieval and Renaissance manuscript books in the Library of Congress, 45 Also available in digital form on the Library of Congress Web site. LC copy: Source: Gift of Edith G. Rosenwald, 1981. LAC ddw 2023-03-14 update (1 card)
